summary:
This case strongly suggests a diagnosis of \textbf{Gerstmann’s Syndrome}, characterized by specific neuropsychological deficits like acalculia and left-right orientation errors due to underlying vascular pathology or multiple sclerosis-related white matter damage. 

The differential should include conditions causing similar neurological presentations but given her age and imaging results, this condition stands out prominently based on both clinical signs and radiographic evidence provided here. 
\boxed{\textbf{Gerstmann's Syndrome}}
